<br>
Gloves of Earthcrafting(PoG Quest)<br>
+10 AC +5 Strength +12 Wisdom +5 Magic Resist +5 Fire Resist +5 Cold Resist +50 Mana  <br>
<br>
Coldain Skin Glovs(Kael Quest/Drop)<br>
+12 AC +9 Stamina +6 Wisdom +6 Intelligence +20 Hit Points +20 Mana<br>
<br>
Woven Grass Gauntlets(SS quest)<br>
+8 AC +2 Stamina +2 Dexterity +3 Wisdom +5 Magic Resist +5 Disease Resist +45 Mana<br>
<br>
Assuming you have access to all three, and that maintianing 200 wis is not an issue, which is best?<br>
<br>
My thoughts, it depends.  (duh)<br>
<br>
For general use: I like coldain skin, better AC/HP without sacrificing much mana.<br>
<br>
For Soloing: I like earthcrafter gloves.  Ever try quading sentient armor?  mana = good<br>
<br>
For fights were resists are an issue, like say in ToV, then I like earthcrafters or SS, depending on which resist I need.<br>
<br>
Your thoughts?<br>
-hs <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/4/01 10:28:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Earthcrafting vs. Coldain Skin vs. Woven Grass</span><hr size=1> Personaly I like the gloves of Earthcrafting.  Not only are resists nice, but the +str helps with all that heavy druid armor.  The high wisdom means you can place resist jewlery as normal gear or drop other wisdom items for high AC.  The effect on the gloves is nice too. <p>Batou Thornhill<BR>
